<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1017,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[373,471,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
is examined from photos from the 
<collectionCode box="[870,958,1198,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">BMNH</collectionCode>
. A male specimen was first recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1233,1257]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[268,464,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1910) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. Vol. 10. Taylor and Francis, London, 829 pp, xix, plates 148 - 173." type="book chapter" year="1910">
Hampson (
<number box="[395,456,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It is labelled as &quot;C. 
<collectingCountry box="[720,790,1233,1257]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">China</collectingCountry>
, Kiukiang, Snowy Valley, W.B. Pryer&quot; and &quot;Chekiang&quot; (provided by Mr. M. R. Honey). There is a discrepancy for the locality between &quot;Kiukiang&quot; (Jiujiang, Jiangxi) and &quot;Snowy Valley&quot; (nr. Ningbo, Zhejiang). Because there is another label, namely &quot;Chekiang&quot;, we report the species from Zhejiang following the advice of M. R. Honey. We also have not found the species in our collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
